data.body:
Running Atom 1.0.19 on Windows, I do `atom --safe C:\Temp\foo.js` to open this non-existing file.  I then enter the following content:

``` js
function foo() {
    // }
}
```

Positioning the cursor on the only opening brace tells me that it incorrectly matches the closing brace in the comment.  And indeed, hitting <kbd>Ctrl-M</kbd> to jump to the matching brace confirms this.

Shouldn't braces in comments be skipped for the purposes of brace matching?
